      1. **Cascaded intent specs** (keep, reword slightly) — specs derived from
         research that cascade through the pipeline
      2. **Cross-project brain** (keep, reword) — domain knowledge persists in
         an Obsidian vault filed by domain, not trapped in a chat window. Rules
         packs have no knowledge layer.
      3. **Auto-learning** (new) — when the fix loop closes, retro findings
         promote to the brain. Rules packs cannot learn from their own failures.
      4. **QA checks output against intent** (keep, already present)
      5. **Coding playbook** (new) — the architect navigates a structured
         convention hierarchy via a dedicated skill. Rules packs are flat
         unstructured text.

      Excluded from LP (available ammunition not shipped):
      - Upgrade command — spec categorizes it as supporting, not headline.
        Better suited for docs or beat 3 annotations if space allows.
      - Misalignment tags — too inside-baseball for a 60-second read.

- [x] Update the summary paragraph below the comparison grid. Current text
